TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimal Order of Servers for Tandem Queues in Light Traffic
AU  - Greenberg, Betsy S.
AU  - Wolff, Ronald W.
Y1  - 1988/04/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.4.500
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.4.500
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 500
EP  - 508
VL  - 34
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We study single-server stations in tandem, in which customers arrive according to a Poisson Process and are to be served at each of two servers. The order of the stations is assumed not to affect the quality of the service customers obtain. Using a light traffic approximation, we select (for various joint distributions of service time) the order of the stations that minimizes expected customer delay.
AB  - We study single-server stations in tandem, in which customers arrive according to a Poisson Process and are to be served at each of two servers. The order of the stations is assumed not to affect the quality of the service customers obtain. Using a light traffic approximation, we select (for various joint distributions of service time) the order of the stations that minimizes expected customer delay.
